      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHERE'S THE LUCK (3) recorded a 4.5 lengths win (17.32) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Looks suited and should go close. MARRA LAD (1) hit the ground running from a squeeze draw and was prominent throughout but faded out of it when 6th at Gosford in a Grade 5. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Better than last start and can bounce back. FUN EFFECTS (2) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind WHERE'S THE LUCK (17.63) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Hard to beat again. REMISSION RUN (6) has won at this course and distance, should be thereabouts.",
